sub_title: Doctoral Candidate in Biomedical Engineering at Eindhoven University of Technology
summary:
Inventive, collaborative, results-oriented professional with a broad scientific background in oncology, immunology and biomedical materials.

Well versed in designing experiments, developing hypotheses, analyzing data, troubleshooting and customizing experimental tools to research questions, reviewing scientific literature, communicating ideas, presenting results and preparing manuscripts.

preparations of liver and fat tissue in dissected piglets.', 'title': 'Research experience on animal tissue sampling and preparation', 'employment_type': None}, {'location': 'Wageningen, Gelderland, Netherlands', 'date': {'start': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}, 'end': {'month': 9, 'day': None, 'year': 2020}}, 'company': 'Wageningen University & Research', 'description': "Due to detrimental cancer-induced cachexia (CC) effects and poor survival prognosis of cachectic cancer patients, there is a need to recognize cachexia early and develop prevention therapies. Furthermore, as mitochondrial dynamics had been reported as one of the initial modified processes, a better understanding of its mediators' regulation is needed. In my thesis, our focus was on gene and protein expression of mitochondrial dynamics related genes and proteins within the cachectic differentiated muscle cells. Additionally, we observed the parallel regulation of cachectic markers between the processes of muscle atrophy, mitochondrial fusion and fission, and myofibers remodelling.\xa0

-Found the knowledge gap and designed the project: aim, hypotheses, methodology.
-Cultured cells, differentiated myoblasts into myotubes, and conditioned them with lipopolysaccharides, used cancer medium or different differentiation media.
-Fixated the cells with formaldehyde and performed fluorescent staining of the cells.
-Used fluorescence and brightfield microscopy to determine myotube width, length, number of nuclei, and mitochondria networks.
-Used Fiji (ImageJ) to analyze the obtained images, data.
-Performed protein extraction, western blot, and antibody staining of the membrane.
-Measured gene expression with RT-qPCR.
-Performed RNA extraction, purification, and cDNA conversion.
-Used GraphPad Prism for statistical analysis and visualization of obtained data.", 'title': 'Master Thesis Project', 'employment_type': None}]}, {'company': {'id': 13016, 'name': 'Jozef Stefan Institute', 'logo': 'https://media.licdn.com/dms/image/C4D0BAQGUx4HQsK01Uw/company-logo_400_400/0/1519856051271?e=1700697600&v=beta&t=UQ_xqrTAHSsAnyN_sFjO5GkHAn60uNsfQn6q04ch8PU', 'url': 'https://www.linkedin.com/company/jozef-stefan-institute/', 'employees': {'start': 501, 'end': 1000}}, 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'profile_positions': [{'location': 'Slovenia', 'date': {'start': {'month': 4, 'day': None, 'year': 2018}, 'end': {'month': 7, 'day': None, 'year': 2019}}, 'company': 'Jozef Stefan Institute', 'description': 'Supervisor: Dr. Saša Novak

1ST PROJECT: Silk Fibroin Hormonal Oscillating Drug Delivery System
I was involved in the development of a new drug-delivering system for hormone
replacement therapy. The selected biomaterial was silk fibroin which naturally
deteriorates in the body and releases different amounts of entrapped hormones,
and therefore more closely imitates the natural excretion of progesterone and
estrogens.

2ND PROJECT: Biodegradable Silk Fibroin Scaffolds, Films, and Hydrogels for stem
cell growth and specialisation
We focused on natural biodegradable materials, such as silk fibroin, that can be
used to treat osteochondral and bone defects, wound treatments, and as a
supporting matter for stem cell growth. The project was held in collaboration
with the Veterinary Faculty of the University of Ljubljana.
Implemented the dialysis for the obtainment of pure silk fibroin without
impurities.
Performed lyophilization.
With different methods obtained, the silk fibrin gels, scaffolds, and films.
Incorporated hormones inside the gel structure of silk fibroin.
Performed the degradation test and estimation of hormone release.

3RD PROJECT: Bioactive glass for bone ingrowth and prevention of implant
loosening
We produced an innovative bioactive glass used in regenerative medicine to
promote bone ingrowth and prevention of implant loosening. In addition, the
bioactive glass was used as a composite in teeth whitening agents, as it helps to
reduce teeth hypersensitivity by regrowing dentine tubules with hydroxyapatite.
The material was later patented, and a spin-off company was established.
Utilized potentiometric titrator for the obtainment of bioactive glass.
Operated high-temperature laboratory oven for calcification of bioactive
